    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="381"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/641</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister (<persName type="from"
                            >Simopoulos</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2145</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-11">November 11,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In reply to your letter dated October 31,
                    1933, by which you kindly transmitted the communication of the Acting Secretary
                    of Treasury relative to my country’s debt to the United States, I have the honor
                    to inform you that, while the Greek Government considers the second loan under
                    the Agreement of May 10, 1929, as a war loan, taking, <pb facs="0651" n="547"
                        xml:id="pg_547"/> however, into consideration the objections of the United
                    States Government on this matter and desiring to avoid any discussions, it would
                    be disposed to grant to this debt the same treatment accorded last year,<note
                        n="12" xml:id="d381fn12">See telegram No. 158, December 31, 1932, from the
                        Chargé in Greece, <ref target="frus1932v02#pg_429">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 429</ref>.</note> expressly
                    maintaining, as in the past, its point of view on the character of this
                        debt.<note n="13" xml:id="d381fn13">See memorandum from the Greek Prime
                        Minister to the American Chargé in Greece, October 8, 1932, <ref
                            target="frus1932v02#pg_402">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 402</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Consequently, the Greek Government will recognize against the interest of this
                    loan due May 10, 1933 and November 10, 1933, the same percentage which will be
                    applied for the stabilization loan.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Simopoulos</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
